rComments: I didn't have very good attendance in the class due to health issues, and he was very accommodating for me and any other students that had missed quizzes. He is very kind and genuinely interested in his students, also enthusiastic about lecture material. Tough marker but worthwhile.

Cannon is an amazing professor.  If you have the option, take one of his courses and I swear you will not be disappointed.  Most of his classes fill up really quickly and they tend to be on the harder side, but it's totally worth it.  He's energetic, funny, cares about his students, and incredibly knowledgeable.

A world class prof.  Schmitt is not only funny, humble, clever, and intelligent, but he really genuinely cares about his students, always has a smile on his face, and makes it a pleasure to come to class.  His passion for his subject, his enthusiasm, his very refined knowledge, helpful slides, and approachability make him one of UofT's favorites.
